{"contents":[{"parts":[{"text":"Tell me a story in 100 words?"}],"role":"user"},{"parts":[{"text":"Rain"}],"role":"model"},{"parts":[{"text":" lashed against the bakery window. Inside, old Mrs. Higgins kneaded dough,"}],"role":"model"},{"parts":[{"text":" her wrinkled hands strong despite their age. A young girl, soaked to the bone, timid"}],"role":"model"},{"parts":[{"text":"ly entered. \"Lost my mitten,\" she mumbled, tears mixing with the rain. Mrs. Higgins smiled, her eyes crinkling at the corners. She pulled"}],"role":"model"},{"parts":[{"text":" a warm, knitted mitten from a forgotten drawer. \"Found it,\" she chuckled, handing it to the girl. The girl’s face lit up, her smile"}],"role":"model"},{"parts":[{"text":" chasing away the gloom. Sometimes, the smallest kindnesses are the warmest.\n"}],"role":"model"},{"parts":[{"text":"What is the title of the story?"}],"role":"user"}],"generationConfig":{}}